#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:1
msgid "Chain Export"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:3
msgid ""
"The Chain Export feature lets you package a built chain as a portable "
"deployment artifact. The current implementation exports a ZIP archive "
"containing everything needed to deploy the chain as a running process in "
"Operaton without any dependency on the Linked Data Explorer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:7
msgid "What gets exported"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:9
msgid ""
"Clicking **Export** on a built chain produces a `chain-export.zip` file with "
"the following contents:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:11
msgid ""
"chain-export.zip\n"
"├── chain.bpmn          BPMN 2.0 process with a BusinessRuleTask per DMN\n"
"├── SVB_*.dmn           DMN file fetched from Operaton\n"
"├── SZW_*.dmn           DMN file fetched from Operaton\n"
"├── RONL_*.dmn          DMN file fetched from Operaton\n"
"└── README.md           Step-by-step deployment instructions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:20
msgid ""
"The BPMN file has one `BusinessRuleTask` per DMN in the chain, wired "
"sequentially from a Start Event to an End Event. Each task carries an "
"`operaton:decisionRef` pointing to the corresponding DMN identifier. The "
"included `README.md` explains the two-step deployment process."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:24
msgid "Exporting a chain"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:26
msgid ""
"Build a chain in the Chain Builder and ensure it shows a valid status (green "
"or amber)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:27
msgid "Click **Export** in the action buttons below the Chain Composer."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:28
msgid "The browser downloads `chain-export.zip` automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:30
msgid ""
"The export works for both DRD-compatible and sequential chains. For DRD-"
"compatible chains, consider also [saving as a DRD]{1} if you want Operaton "
"to handle execution in a single call."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:34
msgid "Deploying the exported package"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:36
msgid ""
"The included `README.md` walks through both steps, but the short version is:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:38
msgid "**Step 1 — deploy the DMN files:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:40
msgid ""
"curl -X POST https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest/deployment/create \\"
"\n"
"  -F \"deployment-name=chain-dmns-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\" \\\n"
"  -F \"enable-duplicate-filtering=true\" \\\n"
"  -F \"data=@SVB_LeeftijdsInformatie.dmn\" \\\n"
"  -F \"data=@SZW_BijstandsnormInformatie.dmn\" \\\n"
"  -F \"data=@RONL_HeusdenpasEindresultaat.dmn\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:49
msgid "**Step 2 — deploy the BPMN process:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:51
msgid ""
"curl -X POST https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest/deployment/create \\"
"\n"
"  -F \"deployment-name=chain-bpmn-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)\" \\\n"
"  -F \"enable-duplicate-filtering=true\" \\\n"
"  -F \"data=@chain.bpmn\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:58
msgid ""
"The two-step order is required: the BPMN references each DMN via "
"`operaton:decisionRef`, and Operaton validates those references during "
"deployment. Deploying the BPMN before the DMNs causes a deployment failure."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:62
msgid "Verifying the deployment"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:64
msgid "After both steps complete, confirm the process is live:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:66
msgid ""
"# Verify DMNs are registered\n"
"curl https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest/decision-definition/key/"
"SVB_LeeftijdsInformatie | jq\n"
"\n"
"# Verify the BPMN process is registered\n"
"curl https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest/process-definition/key/"
"chain-name | jq"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:74
msgid ""
"A successful deployment shows incrementing version numbers on redeployment, "
"and the process appears in **Operaton Cockpit → Processes** with "
"`historyTimeToLive: 180` and `startableInTasklist: true`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:78
msgid "Planned additions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:80
msgid ""
"The following export and deployment capabilities are planned for future "
"releases:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:82
msgid ""
"**BPMN export only** — download just the `chain.bpmn` file without DMN "
"files, for teams that manage DMN deployment separately or use a different "
"DMN registry."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:84
msgid ""
"**Deploy directly from the UI** — a one-click Deploy button that calls the "
"Operaton deployment API directly from the Chain Builder, removing the need "
"to unzip and run curl commands manually. This will require Operaton endpoint "
"configuration in the LDE settings."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Cchain-export.md:86
msgid ""
"**DRD package export** — a ZIP variant for DRD-compatible chains that "
"includes the assembled DRD XML (the unified file with "
"`<informationRequirement>` wiring) rather than individual DMN files."
msgstr ""
